<subSubSection lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="16" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="differential diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Differential diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="16" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Species with face produced forward, yellow, with gena brown. Scutum black, bronze pollinose, with a broad yellow lateral vitta, yellow and black pilose. Scutum yellow, black pilose. Pleuron mostly black except posterior anepisternum yellow on posterior 2/3, katepisternum with a dorsal yellow macula and anepimeron yellow on anterior and dorsomedial sections. Wing hyaline, microtrichose. Abdomen 
<pageBreakToken pageId="15" pageNumber="16" start="start">mainly</pageBreakToken>
black, with a broad yellow lateral margin in terga 1 to 5; tergum 2 with a medial black pollinose macula; terga 3 and 4 with two subanterior fasciate maculae that can eventually meet in the middle with a central yellow vitta (Fig. 26).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
